SIMPLE: morally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morally
<hw>Mor"al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a moral or
ethical sense; according to the rules of morality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By good, good <qex>morally</qex> so called, ⟦ldquo⟧bonum
honestum⟦rdquo⟧ ought chiefly to be understood.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to moral rules; virtuously.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧To live <xex>morally</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In moral qualities; in disposition and character;
<as>as, one who physically and <ex>morally</ex> endures
hardships</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>In a manner calculated to serve as the basis of
action; according to the usual course of things and human judgment;
according to reason and probability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is <qex>morally</qex> impossible for an hypocrite to keep
himself long upon his guard.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>morals</ent>⟦br⟧
